@neural-internet・27  Can we get a round of applause for @Rapido [τ , ⛏] and the rest of the NI team for delivering the much anticipated **Compute 1.4.0 update! **👏🏻 

The first stage of our subnet was to build the infrastructure to onboard hundreds of miners and their gpus to our compute network. We have entered the next stage where Validators can finally allocate (use) the compute resources! This didn't come easy for the devs and after hundreds of hours going back and forth, daily sync ups and sleepless nights - the functionality is live through the 1.4.0 update:

Changelog:
- Revised the Docker validation process by conducting a test container execution.
- Resolved issues regarding seamless allocation.
- Implemented allocation request for a designated miner hotkey.
- Implemented de-allocation functionality.
- Added database of allocated resources for validators.
- Implemented a CLI for resource management (allocation, de-allocation, allocation list, resource list)
- Updated scoring mechanism including scoring for allocated miners.
- Implemented purging of miner hardware details after 20 unanswered specs requests.
- Updated wandb upload for allocated miners.
- Updated README (partial content).

Thanks again to all our miners and validators for your patience and participation in building the decentralized compute network of the future
Very much deserved

```bash

# Add user to the Docker group if there are permission errors:
sudo groupadd docker
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
# If necessary, log in/out, restart docker, kill/restart pm2:
sudo systemctl restart docker
```
